Felix Ikem, Nsukka Acting Provost of the College of Education, Nsukka, Enugu State, Dr. Okwudili Nwosu, has warned newly admitted students to shun cultism, examination malpractice and other related vices, warning that any student caught would be expelled. Nwosu gave the warning in Nsukka, yesterday, during the college’s 13th matriculation ceremony. He said: “This college has zero tolerance for sorting of lecturers after exams, either in cash or in kind, as any student caught will be expelled and the lecturer involved will be sanctioned,” he warned. 